@startuml Sequence_Order_Assignment

actor Admin
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB
actor Tailor

== Admin Assigns Order to Tailor ==

Admin -> Frontend: View Orders
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders
API -> DB: Fetch all orders
DB --> API: Orders list
API --> Frontend: Orders data
Frontend --> Admin: Display orders

Admin -> Frontend: Select Order to Assign
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders/:id
API -> DB: Fetch order details
DB --> API: Order details
API --> Frontend: Order data
Frontend --> Admin: Order details

Admin -> Frontend: View Available Tailors
Frontend -> API: GET /api/tailors
API -> DB: Fetch tailors
DB --> API: Tailors list
API --> Frontend: Tailors data
Frontend --> Admin: Display tailors

Admin -> Frontend: Assign Order to Tailor
Frontend -> API: POST /api/orders/:id/assign-tailor\n(tailorId)
API -> DB: Update order\n(assignedTailor)
DB --> API: Order updated

API -> DB: Create notification for tailor
DB --> API: Notification created

API --> Frontend: Assignment successful
Frontend --> Admin: Success message

== Tailor Receives Notification ==

DB -> Tailor: Notification (via system)
Tailor -> Frontend: View Notifications
Frontend -> API: GET /api/notifications
API -> DB: Fetch notifications
DB --> API: Notifications
API --> Frontend: Notifications list
Frontend --> Tailor: Display notifications

Tailor -> Frontend: View Assigned Orders
Frontend -> API: GET /api/orders/assigned
API -> DB: Fetch orders\n(assignedTailor = tailorId)
DB --> API: Assigned orders
API --> Frontend: Orders list
Frontend --> Tailor: Display assigned orders

note right of DB
  Order Status: "Pending"
  assignedTailor: Tailor ID
end note

@enduml


